<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren Meets Gulf Cooperation Council Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rong Yiren Meets Gulf Cooperation Council Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305142094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1253 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 13 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-President 
Rong Yiren said here today that China attaches importance to its 
friendly relations and cooperation with the Council for the Arab 
States of the Gulf and its member nations. 
  During a meeting with the council's secretary-general Shaykh 
Fahim Bin-Sultan al-Qasimi and his party here this morning, Rong 
said that since reform and opening was initiated over a decade 
ago, China's economy has developed fastly and vigorously. 
  He said that China has a vast market potential and good 
conditions for investment, so economic and trade cooperation 
between China and the council have broad prospects. 
  Rong noted that China welcomes business people from the Gulf 
countries, hoping that they come either for visits or for 
on-the- spot investigations. 
  Rong said that China is willing to further cooperate with 
the 
council and its member nations on the basis of mutual benefit 
and respect so as to learn from each other and progress together. 
  Al-Qasimi said that he and his delegation are satisfied with 
the results of their visit, adding that they, as developing 
countries, also feel proud of China's economic development. 
  He said that they believe bilateral cooperation has a broad 
prospect. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

