<H3> <TI>   Chi Haotian Meets Thai Air Force Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chi Haotian Meets Thai Air Force Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305132094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1252 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 13 (XINHUA) -- Chinese State 
Councillor and Minister of Defense Chi Haotian met here this 
morning with Air Chief Marshal Siriphong Thongyai, commander in 
chief of the Royal Thai Air Force, and his party. 
  Extending his welcome to the Thai guests, Chi said that he 
visited Thailand three times and friendly feelings of the Thai 
people and armed forces towards the Chinese people and armed 
forces left him a deep impression. 
  Chi said that China and Thailand, two important countries in 
Asia, enjoy very good relations with constant bilateral 
exchanges. 
  The development of Sino-Thai friendly relations and 
cooperation is of great significance to safeguarding peace in 
Asia as well as the world. 
  He noted that Siriphong's visit to China will further 
friendly relations between the two countries and the two armed 
forces, and wished for the friendship to last as long as China's 
Chang Jiang River and the Thai Chao Phraya. 
  Siriphong expressed his thanks for the warm reception 
granted 
him and said that Thailand and China, both located in Asia, are 
very important partners sharing many similar points. 
  He said that friendly relations between the two countries 
and 
the two armed forces will continue to be consolidated. 
  General Cao Shuangming, commander of the Air Force of the 
Chinese People's Liberation Army, was present at the meeting. 
  The Thai guests arrived here yesterday at the invitation of 
Cao. 

</TEXT>

