<H3> <TI>   Russian Duma Delegation Visits China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Duma Delegation Visits China </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Rybkin Leaves for Beijing </H4>

<F P=102> OW1405024294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0207 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1405024294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 13 (XINHUA) -- Russian State Duma (lower 
house) Speaker Ivan Rybkin expressed hope today that the 
parliaments of Russia and China will cooperate with each other 
for the happiness of the two peoples. 
  Rybkin, who heads a State Duma delegation on the first visit 
of the legislature to China since its founding four months ago, 
was speaking to reporters at the airport before his departure 
for China. 
  China has things for Russia to learn, he said. 
  Rybkin said he paid great attention to the trip and he hoped 
to see how reforms are being carried out in China's industrial 
and agricultural sectors. 
  The successes China has made in its reforms in industry and 
agriculture are just what Russia is trying to achieve, he added. 
  Chinese Ambassador Wang Jinqing went to the airport to see 
Rybkin off. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-50125 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi094_c_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-094 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Duma Delegation Visits China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Duma Delegation Visits China </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Jiang Zemin Holds Talks With Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> OW1605093194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0907 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 16 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin said here today that China highly treasures its 
good-neighborly relations with Russia and wishes to make joint 
efforts with Russia to push such relations up to a new level. 
  He made the remark when meeting with a delegation of the 
State Duma from the Russian Federation headed by Chairman Ivan 
Rybkin. 
  Extending a warm welcome to Rybkin and his party on their 
visit to China, Jiang said that he expects the chairman's 
current visit to play a positive role in developing bilateral 
good-neighborliness and promoting mutually-beneficial 
cooperation between the two countries. 
  Jiang expressed his happiness with the fresh development of 
the friendship and cooperation between China and Russia over 
recent years and said that both China and Russia, sharing a 
boundary line of over 4,000 kilometers, need a peaceful external 
environment for developing their economies. 
  He said that sustained and stable good-neighborly relations 
between the two countries are in line with the common wishes and 
fundamental interests of the two peoples and also beneficial to 
the peace and stability of the Asia-Pacific region and the rest 
of the world. 
  The leaders and statesmen of the two countries are 
duty-bound 
to fulfill the wishes of the people, Jiang said. 
  The president said he hoped both China and Russia would 
handle bilateral relations from a long-term point of view so as 
to bring into the present good-neighborliness an enduring 
vitality. 
  Rybkin said that the Russian people wish to maintain their 
relations of close cooperation with the Chinese people and the 
Russian State Duma is willing to conduct earnest and 
constructive cooperation and exchanges with the Chinese National 
People's Congress. 
  At noon, Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing also met with the 
delegation. 
  The delegation, which arrived in Beijing last Saturday [14 
May] at the invitation of the NPC Standing Committee, will also 
visit Shanghai and Shenzhen during their 5-day stay in China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

