<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing, Moscow Consult on Consular Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing, Moscow Consult on Consular Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305142494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1404 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 13 (XINHUA) -- China and Russia held 
consultations on consular affairs for the first time here from 
May 11 to 12. 
  The consultations were held between directors of the 
consular 
affairs departments of the two foreign ministries Zhang Hongxi 
and Vinogradov. 
  In a friendly and frank atmosphere, the two sides reached 
consensus on protection of legal interests of citizens and legal 
persons of one country in the other, jointly stopping illegal 
immigrants, cooperation in cracking down on illegal activities 
and crimes committed by citizens of both countries in the 
territories of the two countries, and adding more consular 
affairs offices in both countries. 
  The two sides also exchanged opinions on problems stemming 
from implementing the agreement on visas for citizens of the two 
countries signed between the two governments. 
  Both sides expressed that they are willing to enhance 
contacts and cooperation so as to make more efforts to promote 
bilateral good-neighborly relations and exchanges in various 
fields such as trade. 
  The two sides also agreed to continue consultations on some 
issues through diplomatic channels. 
  Tang Jiaxuan, Chinese vice-foreign minister, met with 
Vinogradov and his party. 

</TEXT>

