<H3> <TI>   Gyaincain Norbu Congratulates Mountaineers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gyaincain Norbu Congratulates Mountaineers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1405015494 Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
1425 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1405015494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lhasa Tibet People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Congratulatory message" from Gyaincain Norbu, chairman of </F>
Tibet Autonomous Region, to the China Tibet Expedition; from the 
"News" program] 
  [Text] I am glad to learn that nine members of the China 
Tibet Expedition which is scaling 14 mountains higher than 8,000 
meters in the world -- (Wangjia), (Ciren Duoji), (Bianba Zhaxi), 
(Daqiong), (Jiabu), (Dajimi), (Renna), (Luoze) and (Akebu) -- 
after a tenacious struggle, reached the top of Mount Xixabangma 
at 1255 hours on 7 May 1994. I hereby extend my warm 
congratulations to you. I hope you will continue to exert 
yourselves, carry forward the traditions of mountaineers of this 
autonomous region, achieve more success in scaling the other 11 
mountains 8,000 meters or higher, and win honor for the people 
of all nationalities in Tibet. 
  [signed] Gyaincain Norbu, chairman of the Tibet Autonomous 
Region and chief adviser to the China Tibet Expedition. 
  [dated] 11 May 1994 

</TEXT>

