<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Speaks on Civic Affairs Work </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Speaks on Civic Affairs Work </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1405192494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0930 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1405192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Liu Zhenying (0491 2182 5391), Central People's </F>
Broadcasting Network reporter; RENMIN RIBAO reporter Chen Weiwei 
(7115 4850 0251), and XINHUA reporter Zou Aiguo (6760 1947 0948)] 
  [Excerpts] Beijing, 12 May (XINHUA) -- The 10th national 
conference on civic affairs, which has been convened by the 
State Council, opened at Huairentang in Zhongnanhai this 
morning. On behalf of the party Central Committee and the State 
Council, Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central 
Committee and state president, extended his cordial regards and 
high respects to representatives attending the current 
conference, advanced units of civic affairs work, advanced 
individuals, and the broad masses of cadres and workers who have 
been working very hard on the civic affairs front. 
  Prior to the opening of the conference, Jiang Zemin, Li 
Peng, 
Zhu Rongji, Hu Jintao, Wen Jiabao, Ren Jianxin, Chi Haotian, Li 
Guixian, Luo Gan, and other leading comrades met with all 
representatives attending the conference and had a group 
photograph taken. 
  The main tasks of the current conference are: Under the 
guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism 
with Chinese characteristics and the party's basic line, the 
conference should implement the guidelines of the 14th CPC 
National Congress and the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC 
Central Committee; sum up work experiences, analyze the 
situation; and study and decide the guiding ideology, strategic 
goals, and working tasks for civic affairs work in the next five 
years and until the end of this century in order to better suit 
the requirements for establishing a socialist market economy; 
serve the reform, development, and stability of our country; and 
make due contributions to attaining the second-step strategic 
objective by the end of this century. 
  Jiang Zemin pointed out in his speech: Civic affairs work is 
very important. Comrade Chen Yi appropriately summed up civic 
affairs work as "helping the party Central Committee overcome 
problems and as solving problems for the people." Jiang Zemin 
said that for decades, comrades on the civic affairs front have 
displayed the spirit of "being like an ox," have served the 
people wholeheartedly, and have worked hard and not been upset 
by criticism. They have struggled in unity and have done a lot 
of arduous and meticulous work in showing concern for and 
solving problems for the masses and alleviating social problems. 
They have made great achievements and have made important 
contributions to ensuring state and social stability, promoting 
reform and opening up, and developing the national economy. The 
party and government are grateful to you, and the people are 
also grateful to you. 
  Jiang Zemin said that the party and the people are placing 
great hopes on the comrades on the civic affairs front. It is 
hoped that you will continue to make progress with a pioneering 
spirit, seriously implement the party's basic line and the 
principle put forward by the party Central Committee this year 
on "seizing the opportunity, deepening reform, opening up wider, 
promoting development, and maintaining stability"; strive to do 
a good job in civic affairs work, and make new contributions to 
the cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics. 
[passage omitted] 
  Today's conference was presided over by State Councillor Li 
Guixian. Entrusted by the State Council, Minister of Civic 
Affairs Doje Cering gave a report to the conference entitled: 
"Speed Up the Reform and Development of Civic Affairs Work, 
Protect People's Basic Living Rights and Interests, Maintain 
Social Stability, and Make Contributions To Attaining the 
Second-Step Strategic Objective." [passage omitted] 
  More than 400 people attended the conference, including 
responsible persons in charge of civic affairs work in various 
provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities; 
representatives of civic affairs departments at various levels; 
representatives of outstanding townships; representatives of 
advanced workers on the civic affairs front; and responsible 
persons from the departments concerned of the party Central 
Committee and the State Council. 

</TEXT>

