<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Send 160-Member Trade Group to Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing To Send 160-Member Trade Group to Hong Kong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305170994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1314 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 13 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese mainland is 
to dispatch a 160-member delegation to Hong Kong to hold a trade 
and investment fair on the 23rd of this month. 
  The members of the delegation headed by Zheng Silin, deputy 
minister [ministry] of foreign trade and economic cooperation 
(MOFTEC), will be from 24 provinces, autonomous regions and 
municipalities, as well as four ministries. 
  This will be the first time for the mainland to sponsor such 
comprehensive negotiations on trade and investment in Hong Kong. 
  A MOFTEC official told a press conference held here today 
that the delegation would bring 760 projects covering 
transportation, energy, light industry, electricity, raw 
material and advanced technology. 
  The delegation is expected to be co-sponsored by MOFTEC and 
the Hong Kong Trade Development Council. 
  Chinese officials will also speak at a seminar on foreign 
investment in China, to be held during the fair. 

</TEXT>

