<H3> <TI>   Sino-British Expert Talks Continue in Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sino-British Expert Talks Continue in Hong Kong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1405121394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1155 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1405121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, May 14 (XINHUA) -- The Sino-British 
talks on Hong Kong's future defense and public order continued 
here today when both sides failed to reach an agreement after a 
four-day talk ending Friday. Sources said the talk would run 
into next week. Chen Zuoer, resident representative of the 
Chinese team of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG), said 
that he felt disappointed that an agreement was not reached 
yesterday as expected. Alan Paul, head of the British expert 
team under the JLG, said that they had a "thorough and in depth" 
discussion over the past few days. 

</TEXT>

