<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tianjin To Upgrade Shopping Facilities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tianjin To Upgrade Shopping Facilities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305130894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1019 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, May 13 (XINHUA) -- Tianjin, China's 
northern port city, has just mapped out a bold plan to upgrade 
its shopping facilities in the upcoming few years to make it an 
international shopping metropolis. 
  According to the plan, Tianjin Municipal Government will 
concentrate on the construction of ten commercial streets, 18 
shopping centers, five large department stores and six wholesale 
markets, which are expected to extend for a dozen kilometers. 
  According to a municipal official, a number of foreign 
investors have shown keen interest in investing in such 
construction. Shopping facilities with two million square meters 
in total floor space like the Huaxing Shopping Building, Fuyu 
Plaza and Olympic Building are being built with overseas 
investment. 
  Tianjin's large-scale construction of shopping facilities 
has 
offered an excellent opportunity for foreign investment, said an 
official from the Municipal Planning Bureau. He said Tianjin 
has a number of golden shopping areas which remain undeveloped. 
Tianjin has stipulated a series of preferential policies for 
foreign investment to develop these areas, he said. 

</TEXT>

