<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   CAS Markets 144 Technical `Advances' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CAS Markets 144 Technical `Advances' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1605101594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0840 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 16 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese Academy of 
Sciences (CAS), the largest national research institution in 
China, today offered 144 new technological advances on the 
market. 
  The new achievements, involving machinery and electronics, 
chemical industry, energy, agriculture, new materials, bio- 
engineering and other industries, represent China's latest 
progress in these fields. 
  CAS vice-president Wang Fusong said today that the 
technologies are chosen from among those developed by its 123 
research institutes nationwide. 
  The offer is part of CAS's efforts to make better use of 
technological achievements and provide new technologies for 
enterprises. 
  In order to meet the country's increasing demand for 
technology, CAS changed its research strategy in 1992 by 
concentrating a considerable number of its scientists on applied 
technological research and application or commercialization of 
their technological achievements. 
  The vice-president said that during the past two years, 
about 
500 enterprises have been set up by CAS, utilizing their 
research achievements and establishing technological cooperation 
with about 3,000 other enterprises over the country, which has 
produced huge economic benefits. 
  "All 144 achievements have been compiled in one CAS 
reference 
guide, and in the future CAS will regularly publish such a book 
containing its technological achievements, which will serve as a 
bridge for technological transfer between the research 
institutes and enterprises," said Wang. 

</TEXT>

