<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Businessmen Give Donations to Scientific Fund </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Businessmen Give Donations to Scientific Fund </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1405141694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1239 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1405141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 14 (XINHUA) -- Four prominent Hong 
Kong businessmen have donated a total of 400 million Hong Kong 
dollars to set up a foundation to reward Chinese scientists who 
have made outstanding achievements. 
  The Ho Leung Ho Lee Foundation was founded by Ho Sin-hang, 
honorary chairman of the Hang Seng Bank Ltd, directors of the 
bank Leung Kau-kui and Ho Tim, and chairman of the board of 
directors Lee Quo-wei. 
  The foundation will offer ten prizes a year for achievements 
in mathematics, physics, chemistry, astronomy, meteorology, 
geology, biology, physiology, medical science and other 
scientific fields. 

</TEXT>

