<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Macao To Construct Industrial Development Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Macao To Construct Industrial Development Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1605151394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1432 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1605151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 16 (XINHUA) -- Infrastructural 
construction of Lin Seng Industrial Development Zone on Macao's 
Coloane Island is going to be started at the end of this month 
and is expected to be completed by next May. 
  According to an official with the project, the industrial 
zone covers an area of 337,000 sq m, of which 120,000 sq m are 
for industrial development, 110,000 sq m for construction of 
roads, some 8,000 sq m for grassland, 30,000 sq m for public 
facilities and the rest for commercial and residential use. 
  Costing an estimated 100 million Macao patacas (13 million 
U.S. dollars), the infrastructural construction mainly covers 
water routes, roads, afforestation, running water facilities, 
power and telecommunications network. 
  The official said, at present, enterprises from the 
Zhongshan 
harbor high-tech development zone, Guangdong Province, have 
handed over six project letters to Macao government for 
approval. These projects cover electronics, machinery, 
battery-making and others. 
  Macao government stipulated that construction terms for all 
projects in the industrial zone would end before 1999, the 
official said. 
  Approved by Macao government in 1975, the industrial zone is 
expected to boost the multi-facet and high-tech industrial 
development in Macao. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

