<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Establish Cultural Fund </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Establish Cultural Fund </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1705143294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1338 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1705143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 17 (XINHUA) -- The Macao Government has 
decided to set up a cultural fund to advance cultural activities 
in the territory, according the latest government bulletin. 
  Concerned regulations will become effective as from today. 
  The bulletin says that the cultural fund is aimed at 
supporting all cultural activities sponsored and organized by 
the cultural institution of the Macao Government. 
  The cultural fund will be operated by an administrative 
management committee, which consists of president, 
vice-president, administrative assistant and cultural training 
officials of the cultural institution of the Macao Government, 
as well as an official from the local government finance 
department, the bulletin says. 
  The bulletin stipulates that the cultural fund will be used 
in organizing Macao International Music Festival, Macao Arts 
Festival, publications of Macao cultural institution, and in 
protecting Macao's cultural relics and commemorative properties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

